      <hedline>
        <hl1>Votes in Congress</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>House roll-call vote (Conn-NJ-NY) on bill to help insurance industry cover losses from future large-scale terrorist attacks, approved 227 to 193 (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Tally Last Week in Connecticut, New Jersey and New York.</p>
        <p>House</p>
        <p>1. Liability: Vote on a bill to help the insurance industry cover losses from future large-scale terrorist attacks. The bill would set up a federal loan program to cover 90 percent of any insurance industry losses over $1 billion. For the first $20 billion in losses, the loans would be repaid through a special assessment on the industry. The bill would impose new restrictions on the ability of any victims of future attacks to collect damages in court against insurers and other businesses. Approved 227 to 193, Nov. 29.</p>
      </block>
